<item>
            <title>[PIG-1291] [zebra] Zebra need to support the virtual column &apos;source_table&apos; for the unsorted table unions also </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1291</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In Pig contrib project zebra,&lt;br/&gt;
 When user do the union of the sorted tables, the resulting table contains a virtual column called  &apos;source_table&apos;.&lt;br/&gt;
Which allows user to know the original table name from where the content of the row of the result table is coming from.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This feature is also very useful for the case when the input tables are not sorted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Based on the discussion with the zebra dev team, it should be easy to implement.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am filing this enhancemnet jira for zebra.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alok&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
